1. Setup the virtual environment (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MzuGMSw8la0)
    or use miniconda(https://docs.conda.io/en/latest/miniconda.html)
*** within a project directory *****
2. Activate virtual environment
3. pip install -U -r requirement.txt
4. create new .env file and copy the content of sample-env
5. python manage.py migrate
6. python manage.py createsuperuser( create user and set password)
7. python manage.py runserver
8. Login with user created in step 6

** run this commands on anaconda terminal
************ Anaconda ************
conda create -n env-name python=3.9     --create new env
conda deactivate        --deactivate env
conda activate anemia     --activate env

************* Django *******************
* python manage.py runserver        --start application
* python manage.py migrate          --apply migration
* python manage.py createsuperuser      --create super user account


